<subSubSection id="4FFC65060B79164878E8F82C2368F785" pageId="9" pageNumber="114" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="0759368D0B79164878E8F82C2368F785" blockId="9.[136,1452,1886,2093]" pageId="9" pageNumber="114">
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B79164878E8F82C26D7F7A1" bold="true" box="[189,397,2030,2056]" pageId="9" pageNumber="114">Taxonomic notes:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName id="C0E64D0E0B79164879FCF82C251AF7A1" authorityName="K. Schumann" authorityYear="1891" box="[425,576,2030,2056]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Sida" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="9" pageNumber="114" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="glaziovii">
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B79164879FCF82C251AF7A1" box="[425,576,2030,2056]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="114">Sida glaziovii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is recognized by its light-yellow foliage and by mericarps covered by yellowish stellate trichomes at the apex and aristae (
<figureCitation id="9FDD2A080B7916487A0EF7D025A5F785" box="[603,767,2066,2092]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="8.[136,229,1957,1979]" captionTargetBox="[196,1391,245,1933]" captionTargetId="figure-54@8.[196,1391,245,1933]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 3. A–E. Sida cordifolia. A. Flower. B.Adaxial surface of leaf. C. Abaxial surface of leaf. D. Branch with leaves and schizocarps. E. Branch with leaves, flowers buds and schizocarps. F–J. Sida dubia. F. Flower. G. Adaxial surface of leaf. H. Abaxial surface of leaf. I. Schizocarps and mericarps. J. Branch with leaves, flowers and buds. K–N. Sida glaziovii. K. Flower. L. Flowers, buds and leaves. M. Branch. N. Buds. Photographs by Martin Grings." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6415493" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6415493/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="114">Figures 3K–N</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="9FDD2A080B7916487B5FF7D02466F785" box="[778,828,2066,2092]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="26.[136,229,1957,1979]" captionTargetBox="[196,1391,245,1933]" captionTargetId="figure-54@26.[196,1391,245,1933]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 14. Mericarps. A. Sida anomala. B. Sida confusa. C. Sida farroupilhensis. D. Sida glaziovii. E. Sida cerradoensis. F. Sida cordifolia. G. Sida dubia. H. Sida linifolia. I. Sida lonchitis. J. Sida nemorensis. K. Sida paradoxa. L. Sida planicaulis. M. Sida potentilloides.N. Sida reitzii. O. Sida regnellii. P. Sida rhombifolia.Q. Sida riedelii. R. Sida rubifolia.S. Sida spinosa.T. Sida tuberculata. U. Sida urens. V. Sida viarum. Photographs by Martin Grings." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6415519" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6415519/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="114">14D</figureCitation>
) (
<bibRefCitation id="63774B7C0B7916487B07F7D0237CF785" author="Krapovickas, A." box="[850,1062,2066,2092]" pageId="9" pageNumber="114" pagination="65 - 118" refId="ref19583" refString="Krapovickas, A. (2014) Nuevas especies de Sida Seccion Sida (Malvaceae). Bonplandia 23: 65 - 118. https: // doi. org / 10.30972 / bon. 232258" type="journal article" year="2014">Krapovickas 2014</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4FFC65060B7A164B78E8FF5C22D1FEE1" pageId="10" pageNumber="115" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="0759368D0B7A164B78E8FF5C22D1FEE1" blockId="10.[136,1452,158,329]" pageId="10" pageNumber="115">
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B7A164B78E8FF5C25AAFF11" bold="true" box="[189,752,158,184]" pageId="10" pageNumber="115">Distribution, habitat and conservation status:</emphasis>
—The species occurs in Northeast, Southeast, Midwest and South of 
<collectingCountry id="7FF1761D0B7A164B78BBFF002668FF75" box="[238,306,194,220]" name="Brazil" pageId="10" pageNumber="115">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="63774B7C0B7A164B7914FF002689FF75" author="Bovini, M. G." box="[321,467,194,220]" pageId="10" pageNumber="115" refId="ref18092" refString="Bovini, M. G. (2020) Sida in Lista de Especies da Flora do Brasil. Jardim Botanico do Rio de Janeiro. Available from: http: // floradobrasil. jbrj. gov. br / jabot / floradobrasil / FB 9206 (accessed 7 July 2020)" type="url" year="2020">Bovini 2020</bibRefCitation>
). This is the first record of 
<taxonomicName id="C0E64D0E0B7A164B7AAAFF0024C2FF75" authorityName="K. Schumann" authorityYear="1891" box="[767,920,194,220]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Sida" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="10" pageNumber="115" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="glaziovii">
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B7A164B7AAAFF0024C2FF75" box="[767,920,194,220]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="115">Sida glaziovii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<collectingRegion id="C522F86F0B7A164B7BE9FF00239CFF74" box="[956,1222,194,221]" country="Brazil" name="Rio Grande do Sul" pageId="10" pageNumber="115">Rio Grande do Sul state</collectingRegion>
where the species is known only from one locality in Coastal grassland (
<figureCitation id="9FDD2A080B7A164B7A9BFF242475FEA8" box="[718,815,230,257]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="12.[136,229,2030,2052]" captionTargetBox="[315,1294,482,1962]" captionTargetId="figure-118@12.[258,1329,425,2006]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 5. Distribution map of Sida glaziovii, S. paradoxa, S. linifolia, S. nemorensis, S. planicaulis, S. potentilloides and S. rubifolia in Rio Grande do Sul state, Brazil." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6415497" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6415497/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="115">Figure 5</figureCitation>
), in ruderal environment. With the available records, the species presents an EOO of 1,017,999.948 Km² and an AOO of 1,500 Km². Although it can be considered Vulnerable (VU) by the AOO, conditions B(a), B(b) and B(c) were not met. So, the species is considered Least Concern (LC).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption id="539966050B7A164B78DDF8422242F78F" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6415495" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6415495" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6415495/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="115" startId="10.[136,229,1920,1942]" targetBox="[248,1340,353,1895]" targetPageId="10">
